-- Japanese Bought Net 55.9 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-05-09T23:55:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/japanese-bought-net-55-9-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended May 4 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 55.9 billion yen ($701.6 million)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 22.1 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 24.2 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 53.8 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 123.3 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 72.9 billion yen in stocks, and bought 921.5 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 725.4
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
